Impromptu market and bread shopping @dupainetdesidees - picked up beautiful fresh strawberries, asparagus and tomatoes as well as terrine, rabbit (!) and more! node.text:
I’m always happy when a new bakery opens in Paris, but was especially happy when @tapisserie_patisserie opened, a new bakery from the @septimeparis team. I love everything about it, from the luscious black currant tart with mousseline cream to the pollen-flecked pistachio cream puffs…although the famous Maple Syrup Tart is worthy of its accolades and even the humble Flan Pâtissier (shown) is terrific. Check out my new blog post on this bakery, where @fannypayre and the team incorporates the flavors of the French countryside into amazing pastries!
.
Link in my profile @davidlebovitz - go to my profile, the tap on the URL🔗there, then the pic of this Flan to check out my blog post
.

Romain said our roadside picnic was the “Meilleur pique-nique en France aujourd’hui.” (“The best picnic in France today.”) I think he’s probably right!😋
🍴🍽
Tomatoes with basil and young garlic, chickpeas with lemon, olive oil, and herring, hummus with za’atar, radishes, roasted eggplant and green beans, and hard-cooked eggs (dessert was mangoes, Charentais melon, and we shared a chocolate éclair from @the_french_bastards) rosé via @beauneimports

node.text: Outstanding lunch this week at @mokonutsbakery catching up with @beauneimports over wine, terrific food, and good company (we worked together for a long time @chezpanisse and always have a lot to talk about😃) Started off with very fresh shrimp with tomatillos and fresh corn, Labneh with za’atar, olive oil and homemade pita bread, line-caught tuna from the Basque region with fresh shelling beans, salicornes (sea beans) and cockles, and finished up with a plate of Moko’s fabulous cookies!
